******
[2]
Date: Tue 8 Sep 2015
Source: The Portugal News Online [edited]
http://theportugalnews.com/news/legionella-outbreak-detected-in-oporto/35857


16 people have been infected with the _Legionella_ bacterium in Oporto, 5 of whom have been admitted to hospital with Legionnaires' disease. 6 cooling towers have been closed off as a result, but the National Health Board has not specified where.

A hotel in the region has been shut down after a French and a Swedish tourist staying at the unit became infected with the bacterium, but the head of the Health Board has said that no link has yet been made between those cases and the others.

